properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 12 at 1:18AM MST until January 13 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...PROLONGED MODERATE TO HEAVY SNOW OVER THE SIERRA MADRE RANGE
THIS WEEKEND...

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations 8 to 10 inches.
Winds gusting as high as 50 mph.

* WHERE...Snowy Range. Especially north and west facing slopes.

* WHEN...Through 5 AM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Patchy blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could bring
down tree branches. The cold wind chills as low as 20 below
zero could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30
minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST MONDAY
